<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Nigh" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Nigh,</orth> adv. 1) near: <cit><quote>grazed his cattle n.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 57" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>never harm . . . come our lovely lady n.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 18</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>grapple with him ere he comes so n.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 1, 61</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>draw n.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>so n. at least,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 151</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to be n.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 341" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 341</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ven 341" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 341</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.180" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 1, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 153</bibl>.<lb />Used as a prepos.: <cit><quote>was not this n. shore?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.216" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 216</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>which is too n. your person,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 2, 72</bibl></cit>.
<lb />2) in a manner touching near, coming home to the heart: <cit><quote>that dost not bite so n. as benefits forgot,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.185" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 185</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) nearly, almost: <cit><quote>n. wrecked upon the sea,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 82</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>well n. worn to pieces with age,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 21</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>well n. dead for me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.4.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 4, 81</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>